250 g Ground Beef
¾ cup Basmati Rice
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
16 g Mexican Seasoning
113 g Corn Kernels
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
2 unit(s) Sour Cream
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.26 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high.
Wash and dry all produce.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To a medium pot, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt. Cover and bring to a boil over high.
Meanwhile, core then cut bell pepper into ½ inch pieces.
Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch pieces.

To the boiling water, stir in rice and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 13-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

In a large non-stick pan, heat 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil over medium-high.
When hot, add beef. Cook for 3-5 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat. Add Mexican Seasoning and cook for 1 min, stirring often, until fragrant.
Season with salt and pepper. Transfer beef to a plate. Set aside.

Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then peppers. Cook for 2-3 min, stirring occasionally, until starting to soften.
Add corn and onions. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender-crisp.

Fluff rice with a fork.
To the pan with veggies, add rice, tomatoes and beef.
Stir together until heated through. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer the beef mixture to a lightly-oiled 9x13-inch baking dish.

Sprinkle casserole with cheddar cheese.
Broil in the middle of the oven for 3-4 min, until cheese melts.
Divide cheesy beef Tex-Mex bake between plates.
Dollop sour cream over top.